## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

This is a textbook case of **"coverage-farming"** — every production method is called, giving 95%+ line coverage, but almost nothing is actually verified. These tests would pass even if the production code returned garbage.

---

### 🔴 CRITICAL — Assertion-Free Tests (Zero Verification)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` | No assertion at all. Passes even if `Save` silently no-ops. |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` | Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price changed. |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` | Removes a product but never verifies it's gone. |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` | Captures the count into a local variable and discards it. Zero assertions. |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | Applies 10% discount to two products, never verifies any price. |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` | Imports data, never checks it was persisted. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_PersistsProduct()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(product, retrieved);
}
```

---

### 🟠 HIGH — Trivial `IsNotNull` Assertions (No Value Verification)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` | Asserts `IsNotNull` but never checks Sku, Name, or Price. A product with wrong data passes. |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` | Asserts the list is not null but not that it contains the correct item or excludes "Gadget". |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` | Asserts not null, never checks count or contents. |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` | Asserts CSV string is not null. Could return `""` or malformed data and pass. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetProduct_ReturnsCorrectProduct()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", result?.Sku);
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result?.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void Search_ReturnsOnlyMatchingProducts()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));
    var results = _catalog.Search("Widget");
    Assert.AreEqual(1, results.Count);
    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", results[0].Sku);
}
```

