### Summary

| Severity | Count | Impact |
|----------|-------|--------|
| 🔴 Critical (no assertions) | 6 | Bugs pass silently — the #1 reason you ship defects at 95% coverage |
| 🟠 High (trivial assertions) | 4 | Only proves code doesn't throw; wrong output goes undetected |
| 🟡 Medium (missing edge cases) | 5+ | Error paths never exercised |

**Root cause:** Every test follows a "call it and move on" pattern. Coverage tools count executed lines, not verified behavior. To fix this suite, every test should assert on the **return value or observable side-effect** of the operation under test.
